ygData.messageBody:
Salutations!

My first character was my ranger but after I while I
got a bit tired of playing her because I don't like to
solo that much and it seemed like she was always
soloing. That's why I made Melwen. Melwen never had to
solo and spent 61 levels in duo or larger group mode.
I like playing her a lot. Recently, though I am
starting to go back to playing my ranger and I'm
having fun with her as well. For me the others are
kind of fill in characters and the druid was mostly
leveled by a friend who quit the game and gave me her
account so I have not played them a lot.

I have actually been in this list twice before but I
tend to come and go. I don't have a very long
attention span sometimes and I'm not very patient.
It's part of the reason I have a terrible time with
Quests and none of my toons have an epic.

I do like to talk though. Some people say that I talk
way to much, but I can't help it. And I have some
little problems that sometimes keeps me from playing
for a while or answering e-mail etc so that kind of
messes things up too, but I'm always glad to be able
to face another day.

As you see I'm rambling already so I'll close for me.

/Hugs
Bran
